The child selector selects all elements that are the children of a specified element.

Example:

ul li:first-child{
        color:red;
    }
    
ul li:last-child{
        color:red;
    }
    
ul li:nth-child(3){
        color:red;
    }

ul li:nth-child(even){
        color:red;
    }
    
ul li:nth-child(odd){
        color:red;
    }
    


    <h1>Access Child In CSS</h1>
    <ul>
        <li>Tutor Joes 1</li>
        <li>Tutor Joes 2</li>
        <li>Tutor Joes 3</li>
        <li>Tutor Joes 4</li>
        <li>Tutor Joes 5</li>
    </ul>
